}}</ref><ref name=twoworlds/> During his time at St. Albans, Gore played on the varsity football team, [[Discus throw|threw discus]] for the track and field team, and participated in basketball, art, and government.<ref name=twoworlds/> During his senior prom in 1965, Gore met the date of a classmate, Mary Elizabeth Aitcheson ([[Tipper Gore|Tipper]]) from nearby [[St. Stephen's & St. Agnes School|St. Agnes]].<ref name=twoworlds/>

==Harvard, Vietnam, journalism, and Vanderbilt (1965-1976)==
===Harvard===
Gore joined [[Harvard University]] in 1965, the only college he had applied to.<ref name=harvardnyt>{{cite web
|url=http://www.nytimes.com/library/politics/camp/062100wh-gore.html
|title=On Campus Torn by 60's, Agonizing Over the Path
|accessdate= 2008-06-22
|author= 
|last=HENNEBERGER
|first=MELINDA 
|authorlink= 
|coauthors= 
|date=June 21, 2000
|work=
|publisher=''[[New York Times]]''
}}</ref> Tipper, whom he had been dating since his senior prom, followed him to Boston, first attending [[Simmons College (Massachusetts)|Garland Junior College]] and later transferring to [[Boston University]] where she majored in psychology.<ref name=dance>{{cite web
|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/campaigns/galleries/lifeofgore/photo7.htm 
|title= Garland Junior College dance photograph
|accessdate= 2008-06-22
|author= 
|last=Howd 
|first=Aimee 
|authorlink= 
|coauthors= 
|date=
|work= 
|publisher=''[[Washington Post]]''
}}</ref><ref name=recast>{{cite web
|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1571/is_31_15/ai_55553468 
|title= Next First Lady Will Recast Role - Tipper Gore and Laura Bush 
|accessdate= 2008-06-22
|author= 
|last=Howd 
|first=Aimee 
|authorlink= 
