|coauthors= 
|date= 1996
|work=
|publisher=''[[CNN]]''
}}</ref> The ''[[Washington Post]]'' described his commencement ceremony as a "[[1960s|Sixties]] period piece" of tradition and chaos. This included the moment when "President Nathan Pusey delivered his time-honored welcoming of the graduates to 'the company of educated men,' [and] hundreds of seniors rose from their folding chairs, [[Raised fist|raised their fists]] in defiance, and walked out."<ref name=serveornot>{{cite web
|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/ac2/wp-dyn/A44095-1999Dec28?language=printer
