|date=March 17, 1998
|work= 
|publisher= ''Science Daily''
}}</ref> During this time, he also became associated with [[Digital Earth]].<ref>{{ cite web |url = http://www.isde5.org/history.htm |title = Digital Earth History |work = The 5th International Symposium on Digital Earth}}</ref>

In 1996 Gore became involved in a [[1996 United States campaign finance controversy|finance controversy]] over his attendance at an event at the [[Buddhist]] [[Hsi Lai Temple]] in [[Hacienda Heights, California]].<ref name=biosen/> In an interview on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Today (NBC program)|Today]]'' the following year, Gore stated that, "I did not know that it was a fund-raiser. I knew it was a political event, and I knew there were finance people that were going to be present, and so that alone should have told me, 'This is inappropriate and this is a mistake; don't do this.' And I take responsibility for that. It was a mistake."<ref name=CNNtemple>{{cite web
|url=http://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/1997/01/24/gore.fundraiser/
|title=Gore Admits Temple Fund-Raiser Was A 'Mistake'
|accessdate= 2008-07-02
|author= 
|last=
|first=
|authorlink= 
|coauthors= 
|date=January 24, 1997
|work= 
|publisher= ''[[CNN]]''
}}</ref> In March 1997, Gore had to explain phone calls which he made to solicit funds for the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] for the 1996 election.<ref name=CNNcalls>{{cite web
|url=http://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/1997/03/02/gore/
