|date=February 25, 2007 
|work= 
|publisher= ''[[Washington Post]]''
}}</ref> After ''An Inconvenient Truth'' was nominated for an Academy Award, [[Donna Brazile]] (Gore's campaign chairwoman from the [[Al Gore presidential campaign, 2000|2000 campaign]]) speculated on the possibility that Gore might announce a possible presidential candidacy during the Oscars.<ref name=>{{cite web
|url=http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2007/02/02/2008-democrats-in-town/
